				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I wanted to expand a bit on that last sentence of mine and say in a couple of minor ways I agree with Gnomercy.<BR>
<BR>
Clerics are already perhaps one of the most refined classes in the game, as far as group/raid roles go.  They heal, and buff,  and rez when the need arises.  That's their thing.<BR>
<BR>
There are classes like oh say Beastlord who don't have a raid role.  There are classes like Paladins who aren't worth the pixels they're displayed with unless you're fighting undead.  There are classes like Wizards and Necros who can't find a group to save their (un)life except in highly specialized scenarios.<BR>
<BR>
I'm waiting for them to further refine other classes that are already honed to fine points like Warriors, Monks, and Enchanters.  <BR>
<BR>
To hell with priorities!  <BR>
<BR>
Xilsharn
