			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have a 54 dwarf cleric that has spent most all of his life soloing and has done well doing so. Never did understand the feelings about them being a bad solo class. Changes like this, and the recent undead DOTs just will make soloing even easier, so they're fine with me.<BR>
<BR>
I do agree that this &quot;battle cleric&quot; route does shortchange the paladins.<BR>
<BR>
Though the changes benefit me, I don't really agree with them.  I don't agree with bleeding a profession's unique abilities over to other professions, it takes away from the character of that profession.<BR>
<BR>
It was noted though that this is in preperation for the PoP release. As the game has progressed it has become easier to kill the higher level mobs in the game because players can deal damage faster. So critter design would be to do more damage faster to kill pesky players :) New critters with higher hitpoints and higher damage maybe means with the present ratio of clerics their mana is going to be drained before being able to defeat the mob, so more players (druids/shamans) are going to be needed to add to healing.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
