			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I explained in my last 2 rants why they are over powered but you are probably a druid yourself, your endless over poweredness has blinded you from seeing the truth! I will explain why again, DRUIDS can SOLO and get GROUPS very EASILY, they have teleports which allow them to get to where they need to go saving them the hassle that most classes have to go through when getting to a hunting location. I have 4 characters a paladin, druid, bard, and enchanter, the druid was by FAR the easiest to level up to 50 by soloing and finding groups, I can't understand how druids ever die when they have sow on. Their direct damage spells are second only to wizards being that they inflict high damage at an efficient mana cost, their DOTs like Winged Death are almost totally unresistable. My 58 druid friend is able to solo 3 or 4 sebillis mobs all at one time using dots and root, this includes krups that don't summon, he is able to get groups fast because groups want an evaccer, snarer, and back up healer, (Now they can be the main healer). They can fit into almost any role the group needs except crowd control. Thorns are a nice addition to since they always do a constant number of damage against anything. In outdoor zones they get awsome and efficient ae spells, allowing them to quad quite for mass exp. On raids they are needed for their circle of seasons spells which give higher resists than the normal buffs, they are needed for quick heals when fighting the big mobs so that clerics can get off their complete heals in time. They have awsome group buffs for raids (The clarity I effect of potg is excellent for the casters, and it even gives the main warrior more hps if he gets symbol and the other effects of Aegolism cast separately.) I just can't see why they should be given more abilities when other classes lack for anything useful.
